  "text": "[56] In the following, we will estimate the influence of strike object height (see Figure 17) and return-stroke current risetime (see Figure 18 ). As seen in Figure 17 , the overall variation of the ratio E z_tall /E z_flat for the case h = 200 m is quite similar to that for h = 100 m (see Figure 16 ). When a current waveform whose risetime is 3 times longer than that of the current waveform proposed by [CITATION_1] is used, the ratio E z_tall /E z_flat increases abruptly between d = 30h and 40h, as seen in Figure 18b and in contrast with Figure 16b . The modified, longer current risetime is longer than h/c = 0.33 ms. As a result, the ratios E z_tall /E z_flat and H j _ tall /H j_flat assymptotically approach 1.34, which is smaller than the far field enhancement factor given by (1 À r top )(c/v + 1)/(1 + r gr ) = 1.5.",
